'''Radim Ne<U+010D>as''' (born 26 August 1969) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[association football|football]] manager and former player. He played for the {{nft|Czech Republic}} four times between 1995 and 2000. Ne<U+010D>as made more than 300 top-flight appearances spanning the existence of the [[Czechoslovak First League]] and the [[Gambrinus liga]]. He became the most expensive player in the history of Czech football in 1992 when [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] signed him from [[FC Ban<U+00ED>k Ostrava|Ban<U+00ED>k Ostrava]] for 25 million [[Czechoslovak koruna]].

==Playing career==
===Club===
Ne<U+010D>as started his professional career at [[FC Ban<U+00ED>k Ostrava|Ban<U+00ED>k Ostrava]] in 1987, where he played for five years.<ref name=jerabek/> One of the highlights of Ne<U+010D>as' time spent at Ostrava was scoring from a free kick at [[Bazaly]] in the first round of the [[1990<U+2013>91 UEFA Cup]] against {{fc|Aston Villa}}.<ref name=highlights>{{cite news |first=Ale<U+0161>|last=Uher|url=http://moravskoslezsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/20080308_fotbal_necas_historie_banik.html|title=Radim Ne<U+010D>as: Nejslavn<U+011B>j<U+0161><U+00ED> Ban<U+00ED>kovec ve slu<U+017E>b<U+00E1>ch Slavie {{cs icon}}|work=denik.cz|date=8 March 2008|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref> The same season, Ne<U+010D>as won the [[Czechoslovak Cup]] with Ostrava.<ref name=jerabek/>

Ne<U+010D>as became the most expensive player in the history of Czech football in 1992, when he left Ostrava for [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] for a fee of 25 million [[Czechoslovak koruna]].<ref name=highlights/><ref name=chrudim/> Two years later, he went to [[FK Hv<U+011B>zda Cheb|Cheb]] and then on to Greek side [[Skoda Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]] in December 1995.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Mastrogiannopoulos, Alexander|title=Greece 1995/96|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grk96.html|date=26 April 2003}}</ref> When he returned to the Czech Republic, he played for [[FK Baumit Jablonec|Jablonec]], where he won the 1997<U+2013>98 [[Czech Republic Football Cup]].<ref name=jerabek>[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=4ErKtwjzyv8C&lpg=PA132&dq=%22Ne%C4%8Das%2C%20Radim%22&pg=PA132#v=onepage&q=%22Ne%C4%8Das,%20Radim%22&f=false Cesk<U+00FD> a ceskoslovensk<U+00FD> fotbal - lexikon osobnost<U+00ED> a klubu]; by Lubo<U+0161> Je<U+0159><U+00E1>bek; Grada Publishing; Prague; 2007; ISBN: 978-80-247-1656-5; via [[Google Books]]</ref> He returned to Slavia in 2000, playing and scoring in the second round of the [[2000<U+2013>01 UEFA Cup]] against [[OFI Crete]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/soccer/news/2000/10/26/uefa_results/|title=UEFA Cup second-round results|work=CNN.com|publisher=CNN|date=26 October 2000|accessdate=11 February 2012}}</ref> In January 2001 he signed for Slovak club [[<U+0160>K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/slovan-ziskal-slavistu-necase-deq-/fotbal.aspx?c=A010110_161118_fotbal_rou|title=Slovan z<U+00ED>skal sl<U+00E1>vistu Ne<U+010D>ase {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=10 January 2001|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref> He played for Bratislava for two years before returning to the Czech Republic in 2003, where he signed for [[Bohemian Football League]] team [[MFK Chrudim|Chrudim]].<ref name=chrudim>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/zaloznik-necas-pomuze-chrudimi-d3m-/fot_dsouteze.aspx?c=A030203_103103_fot_dsouteze_ruz|title=Z<U+00E1>lo<U+017E>n<U+00ED>k Ne<U+010D>as pom<U+016F><U+017E>e Chrudimi {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=3 February 2003|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref>

===International===
Ne<U+010D>as started playing for the national youth teams of [[Czechoslovakia]] in 1984, making a combined total of 47 appearances over four years at age groups from under-15 to under-18. In 1988 he made his first appearance for [[Czechoslovakia national under-21 football team|Czechoslovakia U21]]; he went on to make 28 appearances and score six goals during his four years with the team.<ref name=jerabek/>

He made his full international debut for the {{nft|Czech Republic}} in a [[exhibition game|friendly match]] against {{nft|Slovakia}} on 8 May, 1995. He played in another friendly match later the same year, against {{nft|Kuwait}}, but it was 1998 before he made his third appearance, again in a friendly, this time against {{nft|Slovenia}}. His fourth and final appearance was at the [[2000 Carlsberg Cup]] tournament in a match against {{nft|Mexico}}.<ref name=intl>{{CMFS player|NecasRadimI}}</ref>

