==Management career==
In the summer of 2006, Ne<U+010D>as took over at [[Bohemian Football League]] side [[FK Bohemians Prague (St<U+0159><U+00ED><U+017E>kov)]], replacing [[Lubo<U+0161> Urban]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Radim|last=Trusina|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/necas-bude-trenovat-na-strizkove-d45-/fot_dsouteze.aspx?c=A060628_091224_fot_dsouteze_rou|title=Ne<U+010D>as bude tr<U+00E9>novat na St<U+0159><U+00ED><U+017E>kov<U+011B> {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=28 June 2006|accessdate=9 February 2012}}</ref> However his tenure lasted just five matches before he was dismissed, having lost only once during this period.<ref name=leftboh>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/na-fotbal-nezanevru-rika-necas-dee-/fot_dsouteze.aspx?c=A060913_110522_fot_dsouteze_mah|title=Na fotbal nezanev<U+0159>u, <U+0159><U+00ED>k<U+00E1> Ne<U+010D>as {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=13 September 2006|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref>

Ne<U+010D>as spent some time at [[FC Slovan Liberec|Liberec]] as assistant to manager [[Ladislav <U+0160>korpil]] until they were both sacked, along with other assistant coach [[Lubo<U+0161> Kozel]] in November 2009.<ref name=czechradio>{{cite news |first1=Jan|last1=Kaliba|first2=Petr|last2=Kade<U+0159><U+00E1>bek|url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/zpravy/fotbal/_zprava/655167|title=Tren<U+00E9>r Ladislav <U+0160>korpil skon<U+010D>il v Liberci {{cs icon}}|work=rozhlas.cz|publisher=[[Czech Radio]]|date=7 November 2009|accessdate=11 February 2012}}</ref>

Ne<U+010D>as went to Slovakia to manage [[FK Senica]] in February 2010 during the [[2009<U+2013>10 Slovak Superliga]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/chceme-byt-kolem-desateho-mista-rika-majitel-fotbaloveho-slovacka-p9b-/fotbal.aspx?c=A100225_051139_fotbal_ald|title=Chceme b<U+00FD>t kolem des<U+00E1>t<U+00E9>ho m<U+00ED>sta, <U+0159><U+00ED>k<U+00E1> majitel fotbalov<U+00E9>ho Slov<U+00E1>cka {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=25 February 2011|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref> At the beginning of the 2010<U+2013>11 season he went back to the Czech Republic and joined another Bohemian Football League club, this time [[Arsenal <U+010C>esk<U+00E1> L<U+00ED>pa]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Radek|last=Valenta|url=http://ceskolipsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/novym-trenerem-arsenalu-je-radim-necas20100705.html|title=Nov<U+00FD>m tren<U+00E9>rem Arsenalu je Radim Ne<U+010D>as {{cs icon}}|work=denik.cz|date=5 July 2011|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref> Having steered the club to mid-table safety, with the club in 11th position with just two games remaining, it was announced that Ne<U+010D>as would leave <U+010C>esk<U+00E1> L<U+00ED>pa at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/kouc-necas-v-ceske-lipe-dokoucoval-jeho-nastupcem-bude-korda-pq7-/fot_dsouteze.aspx?c=A110611_093223_fot_dsouteze_ten|title=Kou<U+010D> Ne<U+010D>as v <U+010C>esk<U+00E9> L<U+00ED>p<U+011B> dokou<U+010D>oval, jeho n<U+00E1>stupcem bude Korda {{cs icon}}|work=idnes.cz|publisher=Mlad<U+00E1> fronta DNES|date=11 June 2011|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref>

In the summer of 2011, Ne<U+010D>as joined [[FK Spartak MAS Sezimovo <U+00DA>st<U+00ED>|Sezimovo <U+00DA>st<U+00ED>]] in the [[Czech 2. Liga]] as assistant manager to [[Lubo<U+0161> Z<U+00E1>kostelsk<U+00FD>]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Lubo<U+0161>|last=Dvo<U+0159><U+00E1>k|url=http://www.jihoceskyfotbal.cz/index.php?stranka=archiv&id=5888|title=Ne<U+010D>as: Nab<U+00ED>dka Sezimova <U+00DA>st<U+00ED> m<U+011B> pot<U+011B><U+0161>ila {{cs icon}}|work=jihoceskyfotbal.cz|publisher=|date=|accessdate=11 February 2012}}</ref>

